{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.20",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 20,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 20",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 20 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:1",
      "text": "Then Zophar the Naamathite answered:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:2",
      "text": "“Therefore my thoughts answer me, because of my haste within me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:3",
      "text": "I hear censure which insults me, and out of my understanding a spirit answers me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:4",
      "text": "Do you not know this from of old, since man was placed upon earth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:5",
      "text": "that the exulting of the wicked is short, and the joy of the godless but for a moment?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:6",
      "text": "Though his height mount up to the heavens, and his head reach to the clouds,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:7",
      "text": "he will perish for ever like his own dung; those who have seen him will say, ‘Where is he?’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:8",
      "text": "He will fly away like a dream, and not be found; he will be chased away like a vision of the night.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:9",
      "text": "The eye which saw him will see him no more, nor will his place any more behold him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:10",
      "text": "His children will seek the favor of the poor, and his hands will give back his wealth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:11",
      "text": "His bones are full of youthful vigor, but it will lie down with him in the dust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:12",
      "text": "“Though wickedness is sweet in his mouth, though he hides it under his tongue,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:13",
      "text": "though he is loath to let it go, and holds it in his mouth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:14",
      "text": "yet his food is turned in his stomach; it is the gall of asps within him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:15",
      "text": "He swallows down riches and vomits them up again; God casts them out of his belly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:16",
      "text": "He will suck the poison of asps; the tongue of a viper will kill him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:17",
      "text": "He will not look upon the rivers, the streams flowing with honey and curds.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:18",
      "text": "He will give back the fruit of his toil, and will not swallow it down; from the profit of his trading he will get no enjoyment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:19",
      "text": "For he has crushed and abandoned the poor, he has seized a house which he did not build.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:20",
      "text": "“Because his greed knew no rest, he will not save anything in which he delights.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:21",
      "text": "There was nothing left after he had eaten; therefore his prosperity will not endure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:22",
      "text": "In the fulness of his sufficiency he will be in straits; all the force of misery will come upon him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:23",
      "text": "To fill his belly to the full God will send his fierce anger into him, and rain it upon him as his food.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:24",
      "text": "He will flee from an iron weapon; a bronze arrow will strike him through.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:25",
      "text": "It is drawn forth and comes out of his body, the glittering point comes out of his gall; terrors come upon him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:26",
      "text": "Utter darkness is laid up for his treasures; a fire not blown upon will devour him; what is left in his tent will be consumed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:27",
      "text": "The heavens will reveal his iniquity, and the earth will rise up against him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:28",
      "text": "The possessions of his house will be carried away, dragged off in the day of God's wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.20.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:29",
      "text": "This is the wicked man's portion from God, the heritage decreed for him by God.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
